<subSubSection id="61E41F98FF944B6CFF2FFA4BFCB32161" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="29414C13FF944B6CFF2FFA4BFCB32161" blockId="41.[151,1437,1526,2021]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF944B6CFF2FFA4BFED8207C" bold="true" box="[151,320,1526,1552]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Type Material</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF944B6CFEF6FA4BFE21207C" bold="true" box="[334,441,1526,1552]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">
<typeStatus id="F645F2B1FF944B6CFEF6FA4BFE21207C" box="[334,441,1526,1552]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Syntypes</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
: The Perty Collection (housed at 
<collectionCode id="4FEFD4D6FF944B6CFC97FA4BFCE5207C" box="[815,893,1526,1552]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/a6ms-py1z" name="Zoologische Staatssammlung" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">ZSMC</collectionCode>
) includes two pairs (male and female on a single pin) of specimens that were identified as 
<typeStatus id="F645F2B1FF944B6CFDC1F9A6FD432059" box="[633,731,1563,1589]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF944B6CFCBFF9A7FB802059" authority="Perty" authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[775,1048,1562,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF944B6CFCBFF9A7FC4B2058" box="[775,979,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Penthetria nigrita</emphasis>
Perty
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="4D6F31E2FF944B6CFBF0F9A7FAC72058" author="Reiss, F. &amp; Schacht, W." box="[1096,1375,1562,1588]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" pagination="307 - 312" refId="ref35940" refString="Reiss, F. &amp; Schacht, W. (1983) Die Typen der von J. B. v. Spix und C. F. Ph. v. Martius gesammelten und von M. Perty beschriebenen Dipterenarten (Insecta) in der Zoologischen Staatssammlung Munchen. Spixiana Supplement, 9, 307 - 312." type="journal article" year="1983">Reiss &amp; Schacht (1983)</bibRefCitation>
; several additional, apparently conspecific, specimens without labels are also present in the collection (Dieter Doczkal (
<collectionCode id="4FEFD4D6FF944B6CFF27F9DFFF772010" box="[159,239,1634,1660]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/a6ms-py1z" name="Zoologische Staatssammlung" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">ZSMC</collectionCode>
) pers. comm. 2019). Through the kindness of Marion Kotrba (
<collectionCode id="4FEFD4D6FF944B6CFC7FF9DFFB812010" box="[967,1049,1634,1660]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/a6ms-py1z" name="Zoologische Staatssammlung" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">ZSMC</collectionCode>
), photographs of the two pairs of 
<typeStatus id="F645F2B1FF944B6CFF2FF93AFF6120CD" box="[151,249,1671,1697]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">syntypes</typeStatus>
were provided, including a photograph of one of the labels (“1. / 
<collectingCountry id="51E90C83FF944B6CFC68F93BFB8E20CC" box="[976,1046,1670,1696]" name="Brazil" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Brasil</collectingCountry>
. / P. / 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF944B6CFBEEF93BFB4E20CC" authority="Pty." authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[1110,1238,1670,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">nigrita Pty.</taxonomicName>
”). While the label does not explicitly identify it has a type, it does identify it as 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF944B6CFCF7F916FC6320A9" authority="Perty" authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[847,1019,1707,1733]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF944B6CFCF7F916FC2F20A8" box="[847,951,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">P. nigrita</emphasis>
Perty
</taxonomicName>
as well as indicate that it came from 
<collectingCountry id="51E90C83FF944B6CFF2FF973FF462084" box="[151,222,1742,1768]" name="Brazil" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, which is the type locality given by Perty (1830); concurring with 
<bibRefCitation id="4D6F31E2FF944B6CFC74F973FB422084" author="Reiss, F. &amp; Schacht, W." box="[972,1242,1742,1768]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" pagination="307 - 312" refId="ref35940" refString="Reiss, F. &amp; Schacht, W. (1983) Die Typen der von J. B. v. Spix und C. F. Ph. v. Martius gesammelten und von M. Perty beschriebenen Dipterenarten (Insecta) in der Zoologischen Staatssammlung Munchen. Spixiana Supplement, 9, 307 - 312." type="journal article" year="1983">Reiss &amp; Schacht (1983)</bibRefCitation>
, these specimens are here treated as the 
<typeStatus id="F645F2B1FF944B6CFE2AF94EFE6C2161" box="[402,500,1779,1805]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF944B6CFDA2F94FFCB32161" authority="Perty." authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[538,811,1778,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF944B6CFDA2F94FFD7B2160" box="[538,739,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Penthetria nigrita</emphasis>
Perty.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="61E41F98FF944B6FFF7FF8ABFA0826BA" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="493" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="29414C13FF944B6FFF7FF8ABFA0826BA" blockId="41.[151,1437,1526,2021]" lastBlockId="42.[151,1436,150,214]" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="493" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF944B6CFF7FF8ABFEAC215C" bold="true" box="[199,308,1814,1840]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="4D6F31E2FF944B6CFEFDF8ABFE47215D" author="Hardy, D. E." box="[325,479,1814,1841]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" pagination="367 - 547" refId="ref33819" refString="Hardy, D. E. (1945) Revision of Nearctic Bibionidae, including Neotropical Plecia and Penthetria (Diptera). Kansas University Science Bulletin, 30, 367 - 547." type="journal article" year="1945">Hardy (1945)</bibRefCitation>
noted: “The description of 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF944B6CFC9BF8AAFCF7215C" authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[803,879,1815,1840]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF944B6CFC9BF8AAFCF7215C" box="[803,879,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">nigrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is insufficient to positively identify the species, however, if Perty actually had a 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF944B6CFDBFF887FDE52138" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[519,637,1850,1876]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF944B6CFDBFF887FDE52138" box="[519,637,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Penthetria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
before him there can be little doubt but that it was the common South American species.” However, based on the aforementioned photographs (habitus, wing, head, antennae, mouthparts, and male terminalia) of the 
<typeStatus id="F645F2B1FF944B6CFE76F83EFDA821F1" box="[462,560,1923,1949]" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF944B6CFDEEF83FFCFA21F1" authority="Perty" authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[598,866,1922,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF944B6CFDEEF83FFC8721F0" box="[598,799,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Penthetria nigrita</emphasis>
Perty
</taxonomicName>
, it is clear that the specimens that Perty had before him were, in fact, not 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF944B6CFE36F81BFD9C21AC" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[398,516,1958,1984]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF944B6CFE36F81BFD9C21AC" box="[398,516,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Penthetria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but are conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF944B6CFC9DF81BFB1121AC" authority="Wiedemann. As" authorityName="Wiedemann. As" box="[805,1161,1958,1984]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plagiata">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF944B6CFC9DF81BFC4821AC" box="[805,976,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Plecia plagiata</emphasis>
Wiedemann. As
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF944B6CFB28F81AFB6F21AC" authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[1168,1271,1959,1984]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF944B6CFB28F81AFB6F21AC" box="[1168,1271,1959,1984]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">P. nigrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described in 1830 and 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF944B6CFE9BF876FE042188" box="[291,412,1994,2020]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plagiata">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF944B6CFE9BF876FE042188" box="[291,412,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">P. plagiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described in 1824, 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF944B6CFD14F876FD602188" authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[684,760,1995,2020]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF944B6CFD14F876FD602188" box="[684,760,1995,2020]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">nigrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF944B6CFC0EF877FC662188" baseAuthorityName="Pinto &amp; Amorim" baseAuthorityYear="1996" box="[950,1022,1994,2020]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF944B6CFC0EF877FC662188" box="[950,1022,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">Plecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and becomes a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF944B6FFA30F876FF6C26DD" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Plecia" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="493" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plagiata">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF944B6FFA30F876FF6C26DD" italics="true" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="493" pageId="41" pageNumber="492">P. plagiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Considering this, the Neotropical 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF974B6FFD3AFF2AFD6026DD" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[642,760,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF974B6FFD3AFF2AFD6026DD" box="[642,760,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Penthetria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species previously treated by 
<bibRefCitation id="4D6F31E2FF974B6FFBF7FF2AFB7F26DD" author="Hardy, D. E." box="[1103,1255,150,177]" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" pagination="367 - 547" refId="ref33819" refString="Hardy, D. E. (1945) Revision of Nearctic Bibionidae, including Neotropical Plecia and Penthetria (Diptera). Kansas University Science Bulletin, 30, 367 - 547." type="journal article" year="1945">Hardy (1945)</bibRefCitation>
and subsequent authors as 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF974B6FFEB7FF06FD8226B9" authority="Perty" authorityName="Perty sensu Hardy" authorityYear="1945" box="[271,538,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF974B6FFEB7FF06FE4026B8" box="[271,472,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Penthetria nigrita</emphasis>
Perty
</taxonomicName>
is described under the new name 
<taxonomicName id="EEFE3790FF974B6FFC2FFF06FA9A26B9" authority="Fitzgerald" authorityName="Fitzgerald" authorityYear="2021" box="[919,1282,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Bibionidae" genus="Penthetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neonigrita">
<emphasis id="1B8A9001FF974B6FFC2FFF06FB1126B8" box="[919,1161,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="493">Penthetria neonigrita</emphasis>
Fitzgerald
</taxonomicName>
(see above).
</paragraph>
